LA rain CI and PI

Nao Mimoto - Dept. of Statistics : The University of Akron


larain exampe

  acf1 = acf
  library(TSA)       # load TSA package
  acf = acf1

  data(larain)
  plot(larain)

  length(larain)     # this is n
## [1] 115
  acf(larain)

  1.96/sqrt(length(Y))     # size of the blue line
## [1] 0.1827709
  Y = larain
  upper_PI = mean(Y) + 1.96 * sd(Y) * sqrt(1/length(Y) + 1)
  lower_PI = mean(Y) - 1.96 * sd(Y) * sqrt(1/length(Y) + 1)

  plot(Y, type='o')   # same plot as before
  abline(h=upper_PI, col="blue", lty=2)                # add blue dashed lines for PI
  abline(h=lower_PI, col="blue", lty=2)

  plot(Y, type='o', ylim=c(0,40))
  abline(h=upper_PI, col="blue", lty=2)                
  abline(h=lower_PI, col="blue", lty=2)

  hist(Y)

  sort(Y)
